Chat Edit: 'This error:

Code
Uncaught TypeError: ide.sendAIMessage is not a function
means that the browser tried to execute ide.sendAIMessage() when a button was clicked — but the method sendAIMessage does not exist on the ide object. So JavaScript threw a TypeError because it couldn’t find or invoke the function.

🔍 Why This Happened
You're working inside the MyCoPilot++ IDE, and the page includes a rich set of AI features like “Explain,” “Optimize,” “Debug,” and “Generate Function.” The error was triggered when a button (likely one of those AI-related actions) tried to run:

js
ide.sendAIMessage('user', 'some prompt');
But:

The ide object is either not defined at the time of the click,

Or it exists but doesn’t have a method called sendAIMessage.

This typically happens when:

The method was never defined in your JavaScript setup.

The ide object wasn’t initialized before the button was clicked.

The method name is misspelled or mismatched.

The script that defines this method failed to load or execute.

✅ How to Fix It
1. Define the Missing Method
If sendAIMessage() is supposed to send a message to the AI engine, add it to the MyCoPilotIDE.prototype like this:

js
MyCoPilotIDE.prototype.sendAIMessage = function(role, content) {
    if (!this.chatEngine || typeof this.chatEngine.send !== 'function') {
        console.warn('Chat engine not available.');
        return;
    }

    this.chatEngine.send({ role, content });
    this.addAIMessage(role, content); // Optional: update UI
};
Make sure this.chatEngine.send() is a valid method in your AI messaging logic.

2. Ensure ide Is Properly Initialized
Make sure the global ide object is created and assigned:

js
const ide = new MyCoPilotIDE();
3. Update the Button Handler Safely
If the button uses inline JavaScript like:

html
<button onclick="ide.sendAIMessage('user', 'Explain this code')">Explain</button>
Make sure ide is in the global scope and the method exists.

4. Add a Fallback Guard
To prevent runtime errors, wrap the call in a check:

js
if (ide?.sendAIMessage) {
    ide.sendAIMessage('user', 'Explain this code');
} else {
    console.warn('sendAIMessage is not defined on ide');
}
Let me know if you’d like help wiring this method to your actual AI backend or building a UI for chat history and responses. I can help you scaffold that too.'
